---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, LINKEDIN_URL } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Karthik Mahalingam — engineering leader at Microsoft, writing about AI agents, evaluation, compliance, and governance from a systems perspective."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-header">
				<h1>About Karthik and LatentMesh</h1>
				<p class="role">
					Engineering leader at Microsoft. 19+ years building systems at scale,
					now focused on AI agents, evaluation, compliance, and governance.
				</p>
			</div>

			<section class="about-section">
				<h2>Background</h2>
				<p>
					I work at the intersection of large-scale systems, AI evaluation,
					privacy, and governance. At Microsoft, I lead engineering for Purview
					Data Lifecycle Management — building the services that handle retention,
					compliance, and governance across millions of mailboxes and thousands
					of enterprise tenants. Over the past few years, my work has increasingly
					shifted toward AI: multi-agent systems, evaluation pipelines, RAG/CAG
					architectures, and compliance automation at enterprise scale.
				</p>
				<p>
					Before Microsoft, I spent nearly two decades building and leading
					engineering teams across developer tools, semiconductor systems, and
					enterprise cloud platforms — including Syncfusion and KLA. That
					background shapes how I think about AI: not just as a model problem,
					but as a systems problem.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="about-section">
				<h2>What LatentMesh is about</h2>
				<p>
					LatentMesh is where I write about the problems I work on and around:
					AI agents, system evaluation, safety, privacy, compliance, and the
					distributed systems patterns underneath them. These are notes from
					someone building these systems in practice, not observing them from
					a distance. The questions here are practical: how do you govern agents
					at scale, evaluate them before deployment, and make compliance real
					when AI is in the loop?
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="about-section last">
				<h2>Connect</h2>
				<p>
					LatentMesh is evolving around the hard problems of agent evaluation,
					compliance, and governance. If you're building in this space or thinking
					through these challenges inside your organization, I'd welcome the
					conversation.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-box">
					<p>
						Interested in AI evaluation, compliance, or governance?
					</p>
					<a href={LINKEDIN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						Start a conversation
					</a>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.25rem;
	}

	.about-header {
		padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.about-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2rem);
		font-weight: 800;
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: var(--color-text-primary);
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	.about-header .role {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.about-section {
		padding: 2.5rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.about-section.last {
		border-bottom: none;
		padding-bottom: 3.5rem;
	}

	.about-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		color: var(--color-text-primary);
		font-family: sans-serif;
	}

	.about-section p {
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
	}

	.about-section p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.cta-box {
		background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.cta-box p {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
	}

	.cta-box a {
		display: inline-block;
		background: var(--color-brand);
		color: #fff;
		padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-family: sans-serif;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.cta-box a:hover {
		background: var(--color-brand-hover);
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		main {
			padding: 0 1rem;
		}

		.about-header {
			padding: 2rem 0 1.5rem;
		}

		.about-section {
			padding: 2rem 0;
		}
	}
</style>
